INSERT INTO `songs` VALUES (1,'Royal Diadem','Shower Power','Darkness will fill the face of the earth\nLife would have ended as we know it\nJesus will take His own to heaven\nThe devil will be bound for a thousand years\nWith no one to deceive or influence\nJudgement will begin in the courts of heaven\nEvery name shall appear \nAnd every act shall be considered\nAs Jesus stands between life and death\n\nEvery knee shall bow (shall bow)\nEvery tongue confess\nThe Lord of all (The Lord of all) \nEvery eye shall see the King (see the King)\nin His majesty and glory (and glory)\nBring forth the royal diadem(diadem)\nCrown him Lord of all (Lord of all)\n because He’s worthy (He’s worthy)\nHe’s worthy (He’s worthy)\nThe lamb that was on the cross,\n(on the cross)\nIs now the Lion of the cross\nso show respect\n(show respect)\nsurrounded with victory (victory)\nin his majesty and glory (glory)\nbring forth the royal diadem (diadem)\ncrown Him Lord of all (Lord of all)\nand lift your hands in praise and adoration\nand every eye shall see Him\nand every  knee shall bow down\nand every tongue confess \nthat He is Lord\nand worthy of all praise\n\nAfter a thousand years\nJudgement will be over\nDestinies will be sealed\nThe righteous of God will be vindicated and\nGod shall wipe away all tears\nFor the loved ones who would have not made it to heaven\nAnd a new Jerusalem shall descend\nLike a bride dressed for her bridegroom\nAnd they will see it in sight\nAnd the devil and the false prophet and al the evil\nWill come together and want to fight\nThe new Jerusalem\nA lake of fire and brimstone\nShall consume\nthose that who would have rejected the Son of man\n\nbring forth the royal diadem (the diadem)\ncrown him Lord of all (Lord of all)\nand lift your hands in praise and adoration\nand every eye shall see Him\nand every knee shall bow down\nand every tongue confess that He is Lord\nand worthy are\nand every eye shall see Him\nand every  knee shall bow down\nand every tongue confess that He is Lord\nand worthy are all praise\n\nLadies and gentlemen I give you Jesus\nI give you the Son of man\nNo man can come to the Father\nExcept through Jesus\nHe is the Wonderful Counselor\nThe King of kings\nAnd the Lord of Lords\nH is the Saviour of the world\nLadies and gentlemen only Jesus can save you\nAnd He is worthy  of all the praise\n(He is worthy, he is worthy of all the praise)\nHallelujah','/uploads/1776104991930-563812738.jpg','Zimbabwe','Royal Diadem'),(2,'Mvura','Shower Power','Ndichererewo mvura\nNdine nyota ndarukutika\nAkadaro mwana waMwari\nAchipfuura Samaria\n\nAaaaah\nDai waiziva waunotaura naye\nWaikumbira ndikupewo\nMvura isingapwi\n\nAni naani anonwa mvura yeupenyu\nAchapona \nYandinopa izere inopfachukira\nAhipere\nIwe huya huya huya huya huya \nSezvauri huya huya huya huya\n\nUnodawo mvura\nHere nhasi une nyota here\n(nhasi une nyota here)\nSiya zvese zvauinazvo\n(zvese zvauinazvo)\nUteerere mazwi angu\nUchawana upenyu usingapere mandiri\nChako kutenda mandiri\nUchawana ruponeso\n\nAni naani anonwa mvura yeupenyu\nAchapona \nYandinopa izere inopfachukira\nAhipere\nIwe huya huya huya huya huya \nSezvauri huya huiya huya huya\n\nSiya mitoro yako\nHuya kwandiri mwana we\nIwe huya yeah\n\nAni naani anonwa mvura yeupenyu\nAchapona \nYandinopa izere inopfachukira\n(huya huya huya huya)\nAhipere\n\nAni naani anonwa mvura yeupenyu\nAchapona \nYandinopa izere inopfachukira\nAhipere\nIwe huya huya huya huya  \nSezvauri huya huya huya huya\n Huya kwandiri ndikupewo mvura yeupenyu\n','/uploads/1776108706445-431868564.jpg','Zimbabwe','Mvura'),(3,'Ishe Wangu','The Reedemed Family Zimbabwe','M:\nNdanzwa izwi raShe\nRichindidana\nNderemerwa chose ndoda zororo\nNdizvo ndauya Jesu\nNdisakarurama\nNdiponese(sunungura) \nNdinyaradzei (sunungura)\nNdowana zororo\n\nIshe wangu\nNdinovimba nemi\n(pandinorara Baba)\nIshe wangu\n(muvengi anofamba)\nNdinovimba nemi\n(tumai ngirozi Ishe)\nIshe wangu\n(dzindichengete dzinditungamire)\nNdinovimba nemi\n \nF:\nMawoko aJesu (aShe wangu)\nAnondidana (anondidana)\nNyika yezvitadzo inondisunga (inondisunga)\nNdakasungwa Ishe Jesu (ndakasungwa)\nNdazviramba zvinyangadzo(sunungura)\nSunungurai sunungurai Mwari we\nSunungurai ndipone\n\nAll: Ishe wangu\nF: (ndinovimba nemi)\nF: ndinovimba nemi\nAll: ndinovimba nemi\nM: saka rumbizwai Baba we\nF: rumbidzwai Baba we\nAll: Ishe wangu\nM: (rumbidzwai Ishe wangu)\nM&F:(ndinovimba ndinovimba nemi)\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\n\nAll:\nMusi wekuguma\nKwehupenyu\nZuva richadzima mwedzi uchafa\n\nM&F: oh makore\nAll: Makore achapera\nF: nguva Ishe Baba nguva\nF: nguva ichapera\nAll: Nguva ichapera\nF : Tenzi ndoda kuva nemi\nM: Tenzi ndoda kugara pamuri\nAll: Tenzi ndoda kuva nemi \nF: mumazambara enyu Ishe\nAll: Muhupenyu hwekudenga\nF: muhupenyu Baba hwenyu Baba\n\nM: makarinda mweya wangu\nAll: Ishe wangu\nM: kubvira kare mochenjera kuchema kwangu\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\nM: ndochemera mweya wangu Baba\nF: mweya wangu Baba\nAll: Ishe wangu\nM: iwo mweya wangu Baba\nF: Mweya waaangu\nM: ndochemra mweya  wangu Baba we\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\nF: Mweya waangu\nF: ndinovimba nemi nemi\nAll: Ishe wangu\nM: Munyaradzi wangu\nM: Munyaradzi wangu\nF: ndinovimba nemi\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\nF:mm Munyaradzi wangu ndimi\nM: ndimi munoyera ndimi\nAll: Ishe wangu\nM: ndimi Samatenga ndimi\nF: Muponesi wangu ndimi ndinovimba nemi\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\nTenor: chimera mweya wangu\nF: handina wekuchemera\nAll:  Ishe wangu\nTenor: chimera mweya wangu\nM: Munyaradzi wangu\nF: ndochema kwamuri Baba\nF: ndochema kwamuri Ishe\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\nF: iyemi Jesu ndimi zvose zvangu\nM: ndimi munoyera, ndimi Samatenga\nAll: Ishe wangu\nM: ndochema kwamuri\nF: muri Baba vangu\nF: ndinovimba nemi\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\nTenor: chimera mweya wangu\nF: Munyaradzi wangu\nTenor : chimera mweya wangu\nAll: Ishe wangu\nF: muchengeti wangu\nTenor: chemera mweya wangu\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\nF: ndinovimba nemi Ishe wangu\nAll: Ishe wangu\nF: she wangu ndinovimba nemi\nAll: Ndinovimba nemi\n\nM:Makanaka Jesu\nF:Makanaka Jesu\nM:Makanaka \nF:rumbidzwai Ishe \nM:rumbidzo kwamuri\nM&F: Makanaka Jesu Makanaka Jesu\nHallelujah\n','/uploads/1776108960334-513070999.jpg','Zimbabwe','Chishuwo Chemoyo'),(4,'Come Home','Influence Acappella','Kumba ndinodzoka\nNdasuwa Baba\nNdasuwa runyararo\nNdasuwa mufaro\nKunyangwe nditadze anondida Jesu\nAkangondidana ndodzoka kumba\nKumba ndinodzoka\nNdasuwa Baba\nNdasuwa runyararo\nNdasuwa mufaro\nKunyangwe nditadze anondida Jesu\nAkangondidana ndodzoka kumba\n\n\nThere was a man \nWho lived in a land that is far away\n And one of his sons said to him\nI am ready to be on my own\nKo zvowokumbira nhaka\nBaba vachiri vapenyu\nBut in no time\nHe became to be want\nYet his own father was calling come home\n\nCome home\n(come home come home)\nYour father\n(your father calls you home)\nMmm come home\n(come home come home)\nYour father\n(your father calls you home)\nOh come home mwana Come home mwana\n(come home come home)\nuyelekhaya\n(your father calls you home)\nHome\n(come home come home)\nYour father\n(your father calls you home)\n\nZwana\nHe’s always ready to take you back\nI know the Lord is faithful\nUpon His word\nNo matter if they say \nYou’ve gone too far to return\nBut if you look back \nHe never left you\nNo matter if you robbed\nNo matter if you killed\nNo matter if the world says \nYou’re not worthy of forgiveness\nSmile you have every reason to\nThe lord loves you\n\nHe wants you to come back home\n(come home come home)\nYour father\n(your father calls you home)\nHe wants to come home wena\n(come home come home)\nYour father is calling you back home\n(your father calls you home)\nOh uhelekhaya its safer home\n(come home come home)\nUnder His wings you will live wena\n(your father calls you home)\nDon’t you go back to the ways of your sinnings\n(come home come home)\nOh uhelekhaya wena\n(your father calls you home)\n\n…………………….\n\nNdomuziva Mwari uyu\nAchakuregerera\nAchakarugerera\nAh ndomuziva Mwari\nAchakuregera\nAchakuregerera zvivi zvako','/uploads/1776109165294-233624320.jpg','Zimbabwe','Dzoka Kumba'),(5,'Ramangwana','Stand Music','Oh pane zvatinochemera Baba\nTonamatira hosha\nNzara yatekeshera\nOh ndaneta Baba\nndodawo simba(simba)\n(toda iro simba)\nKurarama kurarama\nHatizive ramangwana\n\nOh Ishe tibatsirei Baba\n(tibatsirei tipei simba)\nOh kurarama kurarama\nHameno ka mangwana\n(ramangwana)\nOh Ishe tibatsirei Baba\n(tibatsirei tipei simba)\nKurarama kurarama\nHatizive po pamangwana\n(ramangwana)\n\nKufamba ndino famba\nPota nenyika nenyika\nAchingori Masango matema\nBaba ndifambisei\nMumwenje reupenyu\nNdivhurirei gonhi \nMuvengi anofara\nNekupembera\nKuona vekwenyu\nVachidzokera shure\nKuona vekenyu vasingawirirane\n\nIshe tibatsirei Baba\n(ndibatsirei tipei simba)\nKurarama kurarama \nHatizivi ramangwana\n(ramangwana)\nOh Ishe tibatsirei\n(tibatsireiwo tipei simba)\nHameno pamangwanani\n\n(ISHE isu tachema)Ishe Ishe\nIsu tachema, oda kutiparadza\n(muvengi oda kuti paradza)\nOh Ishe\n(oh Ishe isu tachema muvengi oda kuti paradza)\nOh oh oh \n\nOh Ishe Ishe Ishe\n(tibatsireiwo tipei simba )\nKurarama kurarama\nHameno ramangwana\n(ramangwana)\nOh Ishe\n(oh Ishe tibatsirei tipei simba)\nKurarama kurarama \nHameno ka mangwana\n(ramangwana)\n','/uploads/1776109351921-687967185.jpg','Zimbabwe','Dangwe'),(6,'Ishe wemadzishe','Firm Faith','Ishe wemadzIshe\nMambo wemadzimambo\n(makavimbika)\nNdimi makakodzera\nMbiri nerukudzo\n\nOh Ishe wangu\n(Ishe wemadzIshe)\nmambo\n(Mambo wemadzimambo)\nmakavimbika\n(Ndimi makakodzera)\n(Mbiri nerukudzo)\n\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai )\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai)\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai Samasimba)\n(ndimi makakodzera mbiri nerukudzo)\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai )\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai)\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai Samasimba)\nNdimi dzose dzorumbidza\n(ndimi makakodzera mbiri nerukudzo)\n\nTapihwa hupenyu isu\n(mupi weupenyu)\nOh tachengetwa\n(muchengeti wedu)\nSaka tinomurumbidza\n(ndimi makakodzera)\n(mbiri norukudzo)\n\nPane zvirwere murapi\n(Murapi mukuru)\nkune vakasungwa ndiye\n(Mudzikinuri wedu)\nTinomurumbidza hee\n(ndimi makakodzera mbiri nerukudzo)\nIshe Ishe\n\nRumbidzwa\n(namatwai)\nNamatwai\n(Namatwai)\nNamatwai \n(namatwai Samatenga)\n(ndimi makakodzera mbiri nerukudzo)\nRumbidzwa\n(namatwai)\nNamatwai\nRumbidzwaiwo\n(namatwai Samatenga)\n(ndimi makakodzera mbiri nerukudzo)\n\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai)\nNamatwai\n(namatwai)\nRumbidzwai\n(Yahweh)\nYahweh\n(Yahweh)\n(ndimi makakodzera mbiri nerukudzo)\n\nYahweh\n(Yahweh)\nJehovah Jaire\n(Jehovah Jaire)\nJehovah Nissi\n(Jehovah Nissi)\nJehovah Rapha\n(Rapha)\n(ndimi makakodzera mbiri nerukudzo\n\nRumbidzwai\n(rumbidzwai)\n(Namatwai)\nNamatwai\n(rumbidzwai Samatenga)\nRumbidzwai\n(ndimi makakodzera )\nNamatwai Ishe\n(mbiri nerukudzo)\n','/uploads/1776109557658-168943361.jpg','Zimbabwe','Shoko Rengirozi'),(7,'Noone cared for me(cover)','Fountainview Academy','If my heart could tell a story\nIf my life would sing a song\nIf I have a testimony\nIf I have anything at all\n\nNo one ever cared for me like Jesus\nHis faithful hand has held me \nall this way\nAnd when Im old and gray \nand, all my days\nAre numbered on the earth\nLet it be known, in You alone\nMy joy was found\n\n\nLet my children tell their children\nLet this be their memory\nThat all my treasure was in heaven\nAnd You were everything to me\n\n\nNo one ever cared for me like Jesus\nHis faithful hand has held me all this way\nAnd when Im old and gray and, all my days\nAre numbered on the earth\nLet it be known, in You alone\nMy joy was found\n\nNo one ever cared for me like Jesus\nHis faithful hand has held me all this way\nAnd when Im old and gray and, all my days\nAre numbered on the earth\nLet it be known, in You alone\nMy joy was found\n','/uploads/1776109958662-277475221.jpg','USA',NULL),(8,'Alinisubiri','Soul Influence','Nilikosea kulinda na kutamani\nNa alama ya walimwengu\nSikufanikiwa walimwengu\nWalinipotosha sikua naye\nAmbapo mwokozi\nAlinitafuta naye\n\nKamwe sitaangalia yapitayo \nNinarudi kwa mwokozi\nNinarudi bila hofu nija\nYa maisha yangu atainyoosha\nNinarudi kwa mwokozi\nNinarudi bila hofu\n\nAlinisubiri\nAlinisubiri\nKumngoja kwa upole \nAlinisubiri\nAlinisubiri\nKumngoja kwa upole\nalinisubiri\n\nTime after time\nI was searching for peace\nIn my life\nI was trying to blame all my mikes\nIn this world I live in\nCertain relationships used me \nUntil I was down\nBut all this time\nSomeone was waiting \nTo free me from all my sins\n\nHe was there all the time\nHe was there all the time\nWaiting patiently in love\nHe was there all the time\n\nHe was there all the time\nHe was there all the time\nWaiting patiently in love\nHe was there all the time\n\nAlinisubiri \nalinisubiri\nkumngoja kwaupole\nAlinisubiri\nAlinisubiri \nAliinisubiri \nHe was there all the time\n','/uploads/1776110676472-585052726.jpg','Zimbabwe','Koba  Mnandi'),(9,'Sarungano','The Reedemed Family Zimbabwe','Ndipo pakaperera sarungano\nMumoyo mangu akapinda\nGumbeze rake rinodziya\nHapana chekutya\nNdipo pakaperera nhamo dzangu\nZvirwere zvese zvinomutya\nZvakare rufu rinomutya \nHapana chekutya \nNdipo pakaperera sarungano\nMumoyo mangu akapinda\nGumbeze rake rinodziya\nHapana chekutya\nNdipo pakaperera nhamo dzangu\nZvirwere zvese zvinomutya\nZvakare rufu rinomutya \nHapana chekutya\n\nMudikani dai wandinzwisisa\nWenazareta ndiye andirwira\nAne rudo runo shamisa\nNdaona minana yakawandisa\nSahwira dai wangonzwisisa\nWenazareta ndiye andirwira\nAne rudo runo shamisa\nNdaona minana yakawandisa\n\nSarungano\nMisodzi yangu yava sarungano\nSarungano\nZvivi zvangu zvavasarungano\nSarungano \nNhamo dznagu dzava sarungano\nSarungano\nNdaona minana yakawandisa\n\nAchazodzoka chete satan ndokumbira Ishe musandisiyawo\nHaa chinenharo chimukomana chiya\nMusazondisiyawo ishe\nPamucharegerera vamwe ndokumbira musandisiyiwo\nPamuchanzwira vamwe tsitsi\nIni ndinzwireiwo baba\n\nIshe makatondiregerera\n(makandiregerera)\nNdisati ndakumbira rugererero\n(ndisati ndatombovapo)\nNdisati ndava panyika pano\nNdisati ndava mudumbu ramai\nPasi pasati parohwa nenyundo\nMaiziva kuti ndichazovapo\nTenzi ndinokutendai makandiregerera zvivi zvangu baba\n\n\nSarungano\nMisodzi yangu yava sarungano\nSarungano\nZvivi zvangu zvavasarungano\n(sarungano)\nSarungano \nNhamo dzangu dzava sarungano\nSarungano\n(zvivi zvangu, ndaona)\nNdaona minana yakawandisa\n(iwe)\n(sarungano)\n\nSarungano\nMisodzi yangu yava sarungano\n(vakatora zvivi zvangu akazviita zvake)\nSarungano\nZvivi zvangu zvavasarungano\n(vamurova nemabwe vamupfekedza korona yeminzwa)\nSarungano \nNhamo dznagu dzava sarungano\n(Vachiti ndiye mutadzi ini ndirini)\nSarungano\n(Ndinomutenda Jesu)\nNdaona minana yakawandisa\n\nNdopakapererawo zvivi zvangu\nSarungano\nDzava ngano\nNepahupombwe nekuba zvese\nZvava ngano sarungano\nHandisiri ini arikurarama\nMandiri ndiMwari\nZvivi zvangu zvavangano\nDzavangano dzavangano\nSarungano\n(ndopakapererawo zvivi zvangu)\nSarungano\n(ndopakapererawo zvivi zvangu)\nSarungano\n(ndopakapererawo zvivi zvangu)\nsarungano','/uploads/1776130466196-674783774.jpg','Zimbabwe','Sarungano'),(10,'Mwari uyu','Stand Music','Ndinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nNdingamuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nNdinomuitirei\r\n\r\nWe made our homes His dwelling\r\nand marked his blood on our doors\r\nDeath knocked all around \r\nBut we were never consumed\r\nIts not by our wisdom that we are here today\r\nall that we may remember \r\nHe is our daily need\r\n\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nAnondichengeta mazuva ose\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nAnondinunura pandinonyura\r\n\r\nAll that our eyes may be opened\r\nSo that we may behold\r\nThe army that fights for us \r\nIts not by our power\r\nThat we are strong today\r\nAll that we may remember\r\nHe is our true supplier\r\n\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nAnondichengeta mazuva ose\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\nAnondinunura pandinonyura\r\n\r\nOh he cares\r\n(oh he cares)\r\nOh he saves\r\n(oh he saves)\r\nLook at my life \r\n(look at my life)\r\nHe turned it around \r\n(He turned it around)\r\nOh he hears when we pray \r\n(when we pray)\r\nLook at my life\r\n(look at my life He heard me)\r\nOh he cares\r\n(oh he cares)\r\nOh that he saves\r\n(oh he saves)\r\nLook at my life \r\n(look at my life)\r\n(He turned it around)\r\nOh he hears everytime I pray \r\n(oh he hears)\r\n(when we pray)\r\n\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\n(Ndinomuitirei Mwari uyu)\r\nAnondichengeta mazuva ose\r\nNdinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\n(Ndinomuitirei Mwari uyu)\r\nOh ndinomuitirei Mwari uyu\r\n(Ndinomuitirei Mwari uyu)\r\n(ndinomuitirei Mwari uyu)\r\nNdinomuitireiwo Mwari uyu\r\nNdingamuitirei\r\nndingamuitireiko\r\n','/uploads/1776134953913-612995952.jpg','Zimbabwe','Mwari uyu'),(11,'Day by day','Guy Penrod','Day by day, and with each passing moment,\r\nStrength I find to meet my trials here;\r\nTrusting in my Father’s wise bestowment,\r\nI’ve no cause for worry or for fear.\r\nHe, whose heart is kind beyond all measure,\r\nGives unto each day what He deems best,\r\nLovingly its part of pain and pleasure,\r\nMingling toil with peace and rest.\r\n\r\nEvery day the Lord Himself is near me,\r\nWith a special mercy for each hour;\r\nAll my cares He fain would bear and cheer me,\r\nHe whose name is Counsellor and Pow’r.\r\nThe protection of His child and treasure\r\nIs a charge that on Himself He laid;\r\n“As thy days, thy strength shall be in measure,”\r\nThis the pledge to me He made.\r\n\r\nHelp me then, in every tribulation,\r\nSo to trust Thy promises, O Lord,\r\nThat I lose not faith’s sweet consolation,\r\nOffered me within Thy holy Word.\r\nHelp me, Lord, when toil and trouble meeting,\r\nE’er to take, as from a father’s hand,\r\nOne by one, the days, the moments fleeting,\r\nTill I reach the promised land.\r\n\r\n','/uploads/1776135633393-408772629.jpeg','USA','Blessed Assurance'),(12,'Your Grace still amazes me','Fountainview Academy','My faithful Father, enduring Friend\r\nYour tender mercy\'s like a river with no end\r\nIt overwhelms me, covers my sin\r\nEach time I come into Your presence\r\nI stand in wonder once again\r\n\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\nYour love is still a mystery\r\nEach day I fall on my knees\r\nCause Your grace still amazes me\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\n\r\nOh, patient Saviour, You make me whole\r\nYou are the Author and the Healer of my soul\r\nWhat can I give You, Lord, what can I say\r\nI know there\'s no way to repay You\r\nOnly to offer You my praise\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\nYour love is still a mystery\r\nEach day I fall on my knees\r\ncause Your grace still amazes me\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\n\r\n\r\nIt\'s deeper, it\'s wider\r\nIt\'s stronger, it\'s higher\r\nIt\'s deeper it\'s wider\r\nIt\'s stronger, it\'s higher than anything my eyes can see\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\nYour love is still a mystery\r\nEach day I fall on my knees\r\ncause Your grace still amazes me\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\n','/uploads/1776136536190-11064525.jpg','USA','Redeemed'),(13,'kudakwashe','Peniel Tambama','Ndingasangana ne nenhamo\r\nNdingakuunhika \r\nJehovah vakatendeka\r\nVake unofudza\r\nNdingapererwa nezano\r\nHaazopererwi\r\nMunhamo nemurufaro\r\nNdichamuteerera\r\n\r\nIshe anoda ndimurumbidze \r\nKuda kwashe kuti ndimurumbidze\r\nMunhamo nemururfaro\r\nNdichamuteerera\r\n\r\nSezvo arinyakusika\r\nMuridzi wezivo\r\nAnoda ndifambe naye\r\nMushoko reidi\r\nMunyika yematambudzo\r\nKana murufaro\r\nAnoda ndivimbe naye\r\nNdifanane naye\r\n\r\nIshe anoda ndimurumbidze \r\nKuda kwashe kuti ndimurumbidze\r\nMunhamo nemurufaro\r\nNdichamutererera\r\nIshe anoda ndimurumbidze \r\nKuda kwashe kuti ndimurumbidze\r\nZvingaoma zvinganaka\r\nNdichamuteerera\r\nNdichamutevera \r\nNdichamutevera\r\nNdichamutevera \r\nNdichamutevera\r\n\r\n','/uploads/1776137541255-325109389.jpg','Zimbabwe',NULL),(14,'I wanna go to heaven','Fountainview Academy','','/uploads/1776138352687-590738389.jpg','USA','Redeemed'),(15,'Zuva','Firm Faith','Zuva rekuguma\r\nVanhu vachamhanya kwazvo\r\nGomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\nPachange pasina nguva\r\nYekumanikidzwa gomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\nZuva rekuguma\r\nVanhu vachamhanya kwese kwese\r\nGomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\nPachange pasina nguva\r\nYekumanikidzwa gomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\n\r\nKuchema kuchema\r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKuchema kwakadiniwo\r\n(Kwatichazoona)\r\nKugeda geda \r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKudemba kwakadiniko\r\nkwatichazoona musi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(tichamira seiko )\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(mambo apinda apo)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(vamwe vofara apinda)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(tichamira sei)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n\r\nZuva rekuguma \r\nVanhu vachamhanya kwazvo\r\nVachida kutiza \r\nNyaya dzotongwa\r\nIwe hama yangu\r\nUchange uripiko\r\nZuva rekuguma \r\nNyaya dzotongwa\r\nUchange uripi Nyaya dzotongwa\r\nnaIshe mambo wedu\r\nzuva rekuguma aha\r\nngatigadzirire\r\nuchange uripi\r\nNyaya dzotongwa naIshe \r\nZuva rekuguma\r\nNgatigadzirire\r\n\r\nKuchema kuchema\r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKuchema kwakadiniwo\r\n(Kwatichazoona)\r\nKuchema kuchema \r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKuchema kwakadiniko\r\nkwatichazoona musi werutongo\r\n(werutongo kana )\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(iiih )\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(werutongo kana)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(aah Hapana anoramba)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(Hapana achatiza)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(Ishe bedzi otonga)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(gadzirira nhasi)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(Ishe kana)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(gadzirira hama yangu)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(Ishe otonga)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(ishe achatonga)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(isu tichaimba)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa \r\n(uchamira Seiko)\r\nmusi werutongo\r\n(Mambo apinda)\r\nKana mhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n',NULL,'Zimbabwe','Munesimba'),(16,'Zuva','Firm Faith','Zuva rekuguma\r\nVanhu vachamhanya kwazvo\r\nGomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\nPachange pasina nguva\r\nYekumanikidzwa gomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\nZuva rekuguma\r\nVanhu vachamhanya kwese kwese\r\nGomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\nPachange pasina nguva\r\nYekumanikidzwa gomo ndiwire\r\nNyanza ndinyudze\r\n\r\nKuchema kuchema\r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKuchema kwakadiniwo\r\n(Kwatichazoona)\r\nKugeda geda \r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKudemba kwakadiniko\r\nkwatichazoona musi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(tichamira seiko )\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(mambo apinda apo)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(vamwe vofara apinda)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(tichamira sei)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n\r\nZuva rekuguma \r\nVanhu vachamhanya kwazvo\r\nVachida kutiza \r\nNyaya dzotongwa\r\nIwe hama yangu\r\nUchange uripiko\r\nZuva rekuguma \r\nNyaya dzotongwa\r\nUchange uripi Nyaya dzotongwa\r\nnaIshe mambo wedu\r\nzuva rekuguma aha\r\nngatigadzirire\r\nuchange uripi\r\nNyaya dzotongwa naIshe \r\nZuva rekuguma\r\nNgatigadzirire\r\n\r\nKuchema kuchema\r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKuchema kwakadiniwo\r\n(Kwatichazoona)\r\nKuchema kuchema \r\n(Kuchema kuchema)\r\nKuchema kwakadiniko\r\nkwatichazoona musi werutongo\r\n(werutongo kana )\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(iiih )\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(werutongo kana)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(aah Hapana anoramba)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(Hapana achatiza)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(Ishe bedzi otonga)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(gadzirira nhasi)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(Ishe kana)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(gadzirira hama yangu)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(Ishe otonga)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(ishe achatonga)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n(isu tichaimba)\r\nMusi werutongo\r\n(dzave kutongwa mhosva)\r\nMhosva dzave kutongwa \r\n(uchamira Seiko)\r\nmusi werutongo\r\n(Mambo apinda)\r\nKana mhosva dzave kutongwa\r\n','/uploads/1776140027432-84656813.jpg','Zimbabwe','Munesimba'),(17,'Zuva Rekuguma','Zimbabwe Prison Services','Zuva rekuguma\r\nTichaona mambo ouya\r\nNekorona zhinji\r\nNgirozi dzichimutevera\r\n\r\nJesu ngaarumbidzwe\r\n(anotonga)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe\r\nKudenga nepasi\r\n(ngarumbidzwe mambo)\r\nNdiyee mambo wemadzimbo\r\n(alelujah)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe \r\nAmen\r\n\r\nHakuna zvezita\r\nRingadanwa pasi\r\nKuponesa\r\nKana rasekuru\r\nBishop n’anga\r\nmuporofita\r\n\r\nJesu ngaarumbidzwe\r\n(anotonga)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe\r\nKudenga nepasi\r\n(ngarumbidzwe mambo)\r\nNdiyee mambo wemadzimbo\r\n(alelujah)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe \r\nAmen\r\n\r\nZvino ngatinzwei izwi ramuponesi\r\nTirarame\r\nNyika ichapfuura\r\nAsi soko rake richagara\r\n\r\nJesu ngaarumbidzwe\r\n(anotonga)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe\r\nKudenga nepasi\r\n(ngarumbidzwe mambo)\r\nNdiyee mambo wemadzimbo\r\n(alelujah)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe \r\nAmen\r\n\r\nAmen anouya \r\nMeso ose achamuona\r\nNaivo vakamubaya\r\nVachamuchemawo\r\nHongu amen\r\n\r\nJesu ngaarumbidzwe\r\n(anotonga)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe\r\nKudenga nepasi\r\n(ngarumbidzwe mambo)\r\nNdiyee mambo wemadzimbo\r\n(alelujah)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe \r\nAmen\r\nJesu ngaarumbidzwe\r\n(anotonga)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe\r\nKudenga nepasi\r\n(ngarumbidzwe mambo)\r\nNdiyee mambo wemadzimbo\r\n(alelujah)\r\nNgaarumbidzwe \r\nAmen\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','/uploads/1776140843859-440318101.jpg','Zimbabwe',NULL),(18,'Ndfiye Ega','The Reedemed Family Zimbabwe','Tese tiri kufara\r\nTasanganiswa newenyasha\r\nHatingagone kumufadza\r\nAsi anongotipa Nyasha\r\n\r\n(Moyo yedu)\r\nMoyo yedu ikayevedzwa\r\n(tichaponeswa)\r\nHama yangu tichaponeswa\r\nMupe nguva yekumutenda\r\nNenyasha dzake dzakawanda\r\n\r\nFara hama\r\nTasanganiswa(tasangana)\r\nNekuda kwake\r\n(nekuda kwenysha dzake)\r\nNekuda kwake \r\nJesu chete\r\n(ndiye anogona)\r\nJesu chete\r\n(ndiye ega)\r\nJesu chete \r\n(ndiye ega)\r\nJesu ega\r\nAnogona kundichanesa\r\nNdiye ega achandiponesa    \r\nFara hama\r\nTasanganiswa(tasangana)\r\nNekuda kwake\r\n(nekuda kwenyasha dzake)\r\nNekuda kwake \r\nJesu chete\r\n(ndiye anogona)\r\nJesu chete\r\n(ndiye ega)\r\nJesu chete \r\n(ndiye ega)\r\nJesu ega\r\nAnogona kundichanesa\r\nNdiye ega achandiponesa\r\n\r\noh hakuna mumwe\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nNdiye ega Jesu\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nAnerudo \r\n(anogona)\r\nMunoshamisa Ishe \r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nMwari wangu\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nNdiye ega\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nanerudo\r\n(anonesesa)\r\nRumbidzwai  ishe\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nNamatwai Ishe\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nNdiye ega\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nanerudo\r\n(Anogona)\r\nRumbidzwai Ishe\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nRumbidzwai \r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nNdiye ndiye\r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nAnerudo \r\n(Anogona)\r\nRumbidzwai \r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nNamatwai \r\n(Ndiye ega)\r\nNdiye ega\r\n(Ndiye ega )\r\nAnerudo\r\nAnogona\r\n\r\n','/uploads/1776527961106-778330128.jpg','Zimbabwe',NULL),(19,'Traveling Home','Firm Faith','When I cross the golden strand\r\nAnd I take my saviour’s hand\r\nI’m gonna walk the streets of glory\r\nIn that home beyond the skies\r\nAnd we’ll gather around His feet\r\nAnd sing praises off repeat\r\nAt the corner of glory avenue and hallelujah street\r\nWhen I cross the golden strand\r\nAnd I take my saviour’s hand\r\nI’m gonna walk the streets of glory\r\nIn that home beyond the skies\r\nWe’ll gather around His feet\r\nGonna sing praises off repeat\r\nAt the corner of glory avenue and hallelujah street\r\n\r\n\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nWhen the trumpet sounds\r\nAnd the dead arise\r\nWe’ll meet them in the skies\r\nOh praise God my soul’s complete\r\nwon’t you come along with me\r\nat the corner of glory avenue\r\nand hallelujah street\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nWhen the trumpet sounds\r\nAnd the dead arise\r\nWe’ll meet them in the skies\r\nOh praise God my soul’s complete\r\nwon’t you come along with me\r\nat the corner of glory avenue\r\nand hallelujah street\r\n\r\nWhen my work on earth is over\r\nAnd I go to the other shore\r\nThus I see my saviour’s face\r\nAnd I sing his redeeming grace\r\nI’ll see James, John and Paul\r\nPeter and Silas amid them all \r\nAt the corner of glory avenue\r\nAnd hallelujah street\r\nWhen my work on earth is over\r\nAnd I go to the other shore\r\nThus, I see my saviour’s face\r\nAnd I sing his redeeming grace\r\nI’ll see James and Paul\r\nPeter and Silas amid them all \r\nAt the corner of glory avenue\r\nAnd the hallelujah street\r\n\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nWhen the trumpet sounds\r\nAnd the dead arise\r\nWe’ll meet them in the skies\r\nOh praise God my soul’s complete\r\nwon’t you come along with me\r\nat the corner of glory avenue\r\nand hallelujah street\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nI’m traveling home\r\nWhen the trumpet sounds\r\nAnd the dead arise\r\nWe’ll meet them in the skies\r\nOh praise God my soul’s complete\r\nwon’t you come along with me\r\nat the corner of glory avenue\r\nand hallelujah street\r\n\r\nat the corner of glory avenue\r\nand hallelujah street\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','/uploads/1776536576072-273373662.jpg','Zimbabwe','Munesimba'),(20,'When The King Comes in','Firm Faith','Called to the feast, by the king are we\r\nSitting where His people will be\r\nHow will it fare\r\nFriends with thee and me\r\nWhen the king comes in\r\nWhen the king comes in\r\nCalled to the feast, by the king are we\r\nSitting where His people will be\r\nHow will it fare\r\nFriends with thee and me\r\nWhen the king comes in\r\nWhen the king comes in\r\n\r\n(Tsitsi hedzi)\r\nTsitsi hedzi dzamira dzoga\r\n(Nezvirwadzo)\r\nNezvirwadzo zvakamira zvoga\r\n(Tsitsi nengoni)\r\nnengoni dzakamira dzoga\r\nMambo apinda\r\nKuzotitonga\r\n\r\nLike lightning’s flash\r\nWill that eastern show\r\nThings hidden long from both friends and foe\r\nJust what we are\r\n Will each neighbour know\r\n(When the king)\r\nWhen the king comes in\r\n(when He comes to take us home)\r\nWhen the king comes in\r\n\r\n(Zvakavigwa)\r\nZvakavigwa zvichaoneswa\r\n(Apo)\r\nApo tapinda pakutongwa\r\n(Zvemumoyo)\r\nZvemumoyo tinozviona\r\nMambo apinda\r\n(iye mambo iye)\r\nKuzotitonga\r\n(Zvakavigwa)\r\nZvakavigwa zvichaoneswa\r\n(Apo)\r\nApo tapinda pakutongwa\r\n(Zvemumoyo)\r\nZvemumoyo tinozviona\r\nMambo apinda\r\n(iye mambo)\r\nKuzotitonga\r\n(kuzotitonga)\r\n(iye mambo)\r\nMambo(hera, hera) apinda\r\n(iye mambo)\r\nKuzotitonga\r\n(mambo iye)\r\nMambo (hera, hera) apinda\r\n(iye mambo)\r\nKuzotitonga\r\n(mambo iye)\r\nMambo(hera, hera, hera) apinda\r\n(iye mambo)\r\nkuzotitonga\r\n','/uploads/1776539315470-733560112.jpg','Zimbabwe','Munesimba');
